        <item>
          <title>Bulls great Bob Love dead at 81 after battle with cancer</title>
          <description><![CDATA[CHICAGO (WGN) — An all-star for the Chicago Bulls in the 1970's, franchise great Bob Love has died at the age of 81 after a long battle with cancer, the team announced Monday. Love played from 1968 to 1976 with the Chicago Bulls and was affectionately nicknamed "Butterbean" for his kind demeanor.]]></description>
